snippet.textDisplay: I lost access to my Yahoo account when the breach happened. Had recovery questions and phone number verification established but for some reason recovery questions are no longer available for use, and I had switched cell providers about a year prior. So my account was completely unaccessible. I attempted to find a way to contact Yahoo but they don't have actual customer service, just an password reset option on the site that endlesspy loops back to cell verification. So then I made my first Twitter account just to contact them. No actual response, just a link the the Web faq that loops to phone verification. I lost a lot of games including GTA V which had just came out for PC.
